# Day 4 – Project 2: Narrator Dialogue
# A short story told entirely through narrator text.
#
# WHAT TO NOTICE:
#   - You can have as many lines of dialogue as you want
#   - The player clicks to advance each line
#   - Blank lines between dialogue are fine — Ren'Py ignores them
#   - The story plays from top to bottom, line by line
# =============================================================================

label start:

    # --- Scene: The mysterious door ---

    "It was a quiet Tuesday afternoon."

    "You were walking home from school when you noticed something strange."

    "There, at the end of the alley, was a door."

    "It was bright purple."

    "It definitely wasn't there yesterday."

    # --- Scene: The choice to investigate ---

    "You walked closer."

    "The door had a small golden sign."

    "The sign read: \"Game Design Club — New Members Welcome.\""

    "You had always wanted to make your own game."

    "You reached out and knocked."

    # --- Scene: The ending ---

    "A moment later, the door swung open."

    "Inside, you could see a room full of computers."

    "Someone at the nearest desk looked up and smiled."

    "\"You must be here about the games,\" they said."

    "\"You have no idea,\" you replied."

